  <brief_title>DAHANCA 28A: Phase I/II Study on Accelerated, Hyperfractionated Radiotherapy With Concomitant Cisplatin and Nimorazole</brief_title>
  <official_title>Phase I/II Study on Accelerated, Hyperfractionated Radiotherapy With Concomitant Cisplatin and Nimorazole for Patients With Stage III-IV p16 Negative Squamous Cell Cancer (SCC) of the Larynx, Pharynx and Oral Cavity</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Danish Head and Neck Cancer Group</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Danish Head and Neck Cancer Group</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      P16 negative cancers continue to have a dismal prognosis despite advances in the treatment of
      head and neck cancer. Acceleration, dose-escalation, hyperfractionation, chemotherapy and
      nimorazole has been shown to improve local control. The purpose of the study i to investigate
      the level of co-morbidity and performance status (PS) that allows the combination of all of
      the above means of treatment intensification
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
